## svg-to-png-live

Windows utility that monitors the clipboard for **SVG markup text**, converts it to **PNG** with configured settings (background color + DPI), replaces the clipboard with the PNG image for paste-anywhere, and optionally auto-saves PNGs to disk.

### Requirements

- Python 3.11+
- Windows 11 (v1 target)
- `resvg.exe` (bundled for production builds; see below)

### Run (dev)

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\\Scripts\\activate
python -m pip install -e .[dev]
svg-to-png-live
```

### `resvg.exe`

The converter expects a `resvg.exe` binary at:

- `vendor/resvg/win64/resvg.exe`

You can also point to a custom location with environment variable:

- `SVG_TO_PNG_LIVE_RESVG_PATH`

### Build Windows `.exe` (PyInstaller)

The build bundles `resvg.exe` and produces a distributable executable.

```bash
python -m pip install -e .[dev]
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\\build_win.ps1
```

- Output: `dist\\SvgToPngLive\\SvgToPngLive.exe` (folder build)\n+- Optional single-file build:\n+\n+```bash\n+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\\build_win.ps1 -OneFile\n+```\n+\n+Optional custom executable icon:\n+- Place `assets\\app.ico` before building.


